SUMMARY:How To Give Your Cat a Bath Toronto Launch
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20190213T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20190213T203000
UID:54705926900
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/how-to-give-your-cat-a-bath-toront
 o-launch-tickets-54705926900\n\nPenguin Random House Canada and Type Books
  in the Junction welcome you to the Toronto celebration of Nicola Winstanl
 ey and John Martz'sHow To Give Your Cat a Bath (in Five Easy Steps)\, ahil
 arious and clever "how-to" in which a little girl and a know-it-all narrat
 or are thwarted by a cat who refuses to take a bath.\n\nWinstanley and Mar
 tz will walk you through the simple steps in this perfect read-aloud pictu
 re book.\n\nStep one: fill the bathStep two: put the cat in the bathStep t
 hree: put shampoo on the catStep four: rinse the catStep five: dry the cat
 Seems simple\, right? One problem: the cat has no intention of doing ANY o
 f these things! Watch as the steps keep changing\, the cat keeps escaping\
 , the girl keeps eating cookies and the mess keeps escalating. Soon it's n
 ot just the cat who needs a bath--it's the whole house!Refreshments will b
 e served. Author and illustrator will sign books following the read-along.
 Accessibility information: Type Junction is a mostly accessible space. No 
 stairs. Washroom is located on the main floor but does not feature grip ba
 rs.
LOCATION:Type Books\, 2887 Dundas Street West\, Toronto\, ON M6P 1Y9
URL:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/how-to-give-your-cat-a-bath-toronto-launch
 -tickets-54705926900
X-SOURCE:Penguin Random House Canada
END:VEVENT
